This paper deals with the transferability of adversarial attacks across different models, which is a common concern in the fields of machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper involves the use of specific attack methods and evaluation metrics, which could also place it in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
